        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32939",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Agreed !\n\nCurrently there is no way to tell default option.\nYou can't use:\n- $opts->days=7 because __set() calls parse()\n- $opts->setOption(\"days\", 7) because setOption() as NOTHING to do with getOption() (!!! it should have been named something like setConfigOption !!!)\n\nThis is how I deal with default option:\n\n$opts->parse();\nif ($opts->days === null) {$opt->days=7;}\n\nThis works, but it is not as convenient as passing default values to Getopt. Also maybe the getUsageMessage() may (if implemented) print the default values.\n\nYou can also extend Zend_Console_Getopt and redeclare getOption($flag) as\npublic function getOption($flag, $default)\nbut: it won't work with $opts->days and it will force you to tell the default value everywhere where you need the option ! So it is not a good solution.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-26T01:47:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-26T01:47:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41852",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=manningc",
                        "name": "manningc",
                        "displayName": "Christopher Manning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I definitely see value in allowing the setting of default values, though none of those solutions seem ideal.\r\n\r\nI like the solution of changing getOption to:\r\npublic function getOption($flag, $default = null)\r\n\r\nand I see the downside of having __get not have that default option, but the way you get request parameters works the same in Zend_Controller_Request_Abstract L:235 where __get (Zend_Controller_Request_Http) doesn't have the default variable option.\r\n\r\nSo, following that approach seems like it would be best.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=manningc",
                        "name": "manningc",
                        "displayName": "Christopher Manning",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-08-03T13:21:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-08-03T13:21:06.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
